= Present tense and negation

The present tense is enough to say a lot in Dutch. Once you can combine it with `niet` and `geen`, you can already build useful everyday sentences.

== Regular present tense

Most Dutch dictionary forms end in `-en`: `werken`, `leren`, `wonen`. To make the present tense, start from the stem.

- `werken` -> stem `werk`
- `leren` -> stem `leer`
- `wonen` -> stem `woon`

#let werken-table = table(
