  [jullie], [werken],
  [zij / ze], [werken],
)

#figure(caption: [Present tense of `werken`], werken-table)

After the verb, `jij` often drops the written `-t` in questions or inversion:

- `Werk jij morgen?`
- `Morgen werk jij thuis.`

== Two very common irregular verbs

